    <statement><p>Simplify this expression.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{y}{x} }{ r } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ y }{ \frac{x}{r} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{y}{xr}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{yr}{x}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><alert>Problem 1</alert></p>
<p>We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by <m>x</m>, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{ \frac{y}{x} }{ r } 
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{y}{x} \cdot x }{ r \cdot x } \\
      \amp = {\frac{y}{xr}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p><alert>Problem 2</alert></p>
<p>We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by <m>r</m>, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   \frac{ y }{ \frac{x}{r} } 
      \amp = \frac{ y \cdot r } { \frac{x}{r} \cdot r }\\
      \amp = {\frac{yr}{x}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
